         <listPerson>
            <person sex="1">
               <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1" type="birth">ሓጎስ፡ ተፈሪ፡</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n1" type="normalized">Ḥāgos Tafari</persName>
               <persName><roleName type="title">daǧǧāzmāč</roleName></persName>
               <occupation type="political">officer</occupation>
               <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
               <faith type="EOTC"/>
         
             
               <floruit notBefore="1890" notAfter="1930">He was one of the leading officials of<placeName ref="LOC1236Agama"/>in the late 19th and early 20th century. 
                  Very little is known about the background of Ḥāgos Tafari. In the early <date>1890</date>'s he began to play active role as an officer of 
                  <roleName type="title">rās</roleName><persName ref="PRS8668SebhatA"/>. This alliance was, however, short lived and soon joined the supporters of
                  <roleName type="title">šum ʿagama</roleName><persName ref="PRS9296Tasfayh"/>. He repeatedly switched alliance between the two until the Italian arrived in the region.
                  At time he offered both <roleName type="title">rās</roleName><persName ref="PRS8668SebhatA"/> and 
                  <roleName type="title">šum ʿagama</roleName><persName ref="PRS9296Tasfayh"/>his services and fought against the Italians. 
                  Finally, he recalled to <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/> and sentenced to confinement at <placeName ref="LOC1402AmbaSe"/>. Nothing is known about him thereafter.          
               </floruit>
     
            </person>
